From: Petr Wozniak <petr.wozniak@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 29 May 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: allow BTWT membership join in AP mode regardless of he_btwt_supported

In AP mode, ieee80211_s1g_rx_twt_setup() silently discards incoming
Broadcast TWT membership join requests from STAs when
bss_conf->he_btwt_supported is FALSE, sending no response.

he_btwt_supported is set from NL80211_ATTR_HE_CAPABILITY in
ieee80211_start_ap(). For MLO AP, the start_ap nl80211 path may not
include the HE capability with BCAST_TWT even though the driver (mt7996)
always advertises IEEE80211_HE_MAC_CAP2_BCAST_TWT in AP mode and the
beacon correctly includes "Broadcast TWT" in HE MAC Capabilities.

Result: AP advertises BCAST_TWT to clients, clients send TWT Setup
membership join, AP silently drops the request — member_cnt stays 0.

Fix: skip the he_btwt gate in AP mode. The AP has already advertised
BCAST_TWT in its beacon; the he_btwt_supported flag may not reflect the
actual hardware capability for MLO AP links. The driver callback
mt7996_mac_btwt_setup() will REJECT if the BTWT group ID doesn't exist.

Signed-off-by: Petr Wozniak <petr.wozniak@gmail.com>
---
 net/mac80211/s1g.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/net/mac80211/s1g.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/s1g.c
@@ -181,9 +181,10 @@
 	rcu_read_unlock();

 	if (twt->control & IEEE80211_TWT_CONTROL_NEG_TYPE_BROADCAST) {
-		if (!he_btwt)
+		if (!he_btwt && sdata->vif.type != NL80211_IFTYPE_AP)
 			return;

-		if ((le16_get_bits(twt_agrt->req_type, IEEE80211_TWT_REQTYPE_BTWT_RECM) ==
-		    IEEE80211_BTWT_RECOMM_RTWT_SP) && !eht_rtwt)
+		if ((le16_get_bits(twt_agrt->req_type, IEEE80211_TWT_REQTYPE_BTWT_RECM) ==
+		    IEEE80211_BTWT_RECOMM_RTWT_SP) && !eht_rtwt &&
+		    sdata->vif.type != NL80211_IFTYPE_AP)
 			return;

 		if ((le16_get_bits(twt_agrt->req_type, IEEE80211_TWT_REQTYPE_BTWT_RECM) ==
